## 🧩 What is an Array?

> **An array** is a collection of elements of the **same data type**,
> stored in **contiguous (continuous) memory locations**.
> Its size is **fixed at runtime** and cannot be changed.

---

## 🔑 Quick Reference

| 🏷️ Property | 📋 Detail |
|:------------|:----------|
| 📌 Access | `arrayName[index]` |
| 📝 Syntax | `dataType[] arrayName;` |
| 🏗️ Instantiation | `int[] rollno = new int[40];` |
| 📦 Storage | Contiguous memory |
| 🔒 Size | Fixed at compile time |

